05/09/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Gezim Ostreni, chairman of the co-ordinating body for weaponry collection in Macedonia, announced on Thursday (4 September) the start of a media campaign urging the voluntary surrender of illegal weapons.
The campaign will consist of video and radio clips, print materials translated into several languages, and billboards and posters aimed at increasing public awareness concerning the issue.
The actual weapon collections would begin on 15 November.
It is estimated that as many as 170,000 private citizens possess unregistered weapons in Macedonia.
(Dnevnik - 05/09/03;
MIA, A1 TV - 04/09/03)
